0researchers%20blame%20human-set%20fires%20for%20their%20extinction%2C%20but%20others%20are%20skeptical.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20about%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftarpits.org%2Fresearch-collections%2Ftar-pits-our-research%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E50%2C000%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20animals%2C%20vegetation%2C%20and%20other%20debris%20managed%20to%20get%20stuck%20in%20the%20sticky%20substance%20of%20the%20Rancho%20La%20Brea%20tar%20pits%20in%20present-day%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20millions%20of%20fossils%20found%20in%20the%20pits%20give%20scientists%20a%20time%20machine%20into%20the%20ancient%20past%20and%20reveal%20a%20mysterious%20mass%20extinction%20about%2013%2C000%20years%20ago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecies%20including%20dire%20wolves%2C%20sabertooth%20cats%2C%20and%20camels%20simply%20vanished%20from%20the%20local%20archeological%20record.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20various%20theories%20about%20what%20caused%20so%20many%20megafauna%20%E2%80%94%20large%20animals%20that%20weigh%20at%20least%2097%20pounds%20as%20adults%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20to%20go%20extinct%20at%20around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20from%20the%20warming%20climate%20to%20human%20hunters%20to%20disease.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.abo3594%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20that%2C%20at%20least%20in%20this%20region%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20human-made%20fires%20may%20be%20to%20blame.%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2013%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20there%20was%20a%20huge%20spike%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20carbon%20found%20in%20a%20nearby%20lake.%20Fires%20likely%20caused%20the%20increase%2C%20lead%20author%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.marshall.edu%2Fokeefef%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EF.%20Robin%20O'Keefe%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%2C%20and%20humans%20could've%20set%20those%20fires.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHumans%20have%20a%20direct%20effect%20in%20lighting%20fires%2C%20but%20they%20also%20have%20an%20indirect%20effect%20by%20killing%20off%20the%20herbivores%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Keefe%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20while%20all%20that's%20happening%2C%20it's%20also%20getting%20a%20lot%20warmer%20and%20a%20lot%20drier.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMissing%20dire%20wolves%20and%20constant%20coyotes%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20over%20100%20pits%20in%20Rancho%20La%20Brea's%2023-acre%20park%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnhm.org%2Fperson%2Fdunn-regan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERegan%20Dunn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20assistant%20curator%20at%20the%20La%20Brea%20Tar%20Pits%20and%20Museum%20and%20a%20co-author%20on%20the%20paper%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tar%20is%20actually%20naturally%20occurring%20asphalt%2C%20a%20low-grade%20crude%20oil%20bubbling%20up%20from%20the%20oil%20field%20below%20through.%20Eventually%2C%20water%20or%20leaves%20covered%20the%20muck.%20Unwitting%20animals%20stopped%20for%20a%20drink%20or%20tried%20to%20cross%2C%20becoming%20trapped.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20too%20much%20water%20flooded%20a%20tar%20pit%2C%20it%20no%20longer%20captured%20animals.%20So%2C%20each%20pit%20is%20its%20own%20snapshot%20of%20an%20era%2C%20some%2050%2C000%20years%20old%2C%20some%20more%20recent.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20kind%20of%20these%20discreet%20little%20tornadoes%20of%20fossil%20bone%20concentrations%2C%26quot%3B%20Dunn%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20a%20bright%20orange%20vest%20stands%20near%20Lake%20Pit%20at%20the%20La%20Brea%20Tar%20Pits%20with%20a%20model%20of%20a%20mastodon%20nearby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ddbf194ef9f30019f8c4ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStatues%20of%20megafaunal%20mammals%20give%20La%20Brea%20Tar%20Pit%20visitors%20a%20sense%20of%20what%20animals%20roamed%20the%20area%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago.%3Cp%3EJae%20C.%20Hong%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPit%2061%2F67%20is%20where%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20animals%20in%20the%20study%20came%20from.%20Researchers%20excavated%20it%20between%201913%20and%201915%2C%20finding%20a%20trove%20of%20fossils.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study's%20radiocarbon%20dating%20of%20the%20pit's%20bones%20showed%20an%20interesting%20trend.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20lots%20and%20lots%20of%20megafauna%2C%20dire%20wolves%2C%20saber%20tooth%20cats%2C%20horses%2C%20bison%2C%20and%20coyotes%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Keefe%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20suddenly%20that%20just%20stops%20and%20it's%20just%20coyotes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20around%2013%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20they%20were%20all%20gone.%20The%20pit%20had%20captured%20not%20just%20the%20animals%2C%20but%20evidence%20of%20an%20extinction%20event%20that%20the%20researchers%20think%20was%20due%20to%20human-made%20fires.%20But%20other%20experts%20are%20skeptical%20that%20humans%20were%20the%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20paper%2C%20the%20authors%20wanted%20to%20study%20anything%20in%20the%20environment%20that%20may%20have%20contributed%20to%20the%20megafaunal%20extinction%2C%20including%20temperature%2C%20precipitation%2C%20vegetation%20changes%2C%20and%20fire%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20a%20fuller%20picture%20of%20the%20megafauna's%20landscape%2C%20they%20looked%20at%20a%20nearby%20lake%20%E2%80%94%20Lake%20Elsinore.%20Elsinore%20is%20the%20name%20of%20the%20castle%20in%20%26quot%3BHamlet%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20play%20where%20nearly%20every%20character%20dies.%20There's%20something%20poetic%20about%20using%20a%20lake%20with%20the%20same%20name%20in%20extinction%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2013%2C200%20years%20ago%2C%20charcoal%20accumulation%20rates%20at%20Lake%20Elsinore%20increased%20by%2030%20times%20earlier%20amounts.%20The%20spike%20lasted%20about%20300%20years.%20There%20may%20have%20been%20catastrophic%20fires%20or%20lots%20of%20smaller%20fires%2C%20O'Keefe%20said.%20During%20heavy%20rainfall%2C%20runoff%20thick%20with%20charcoal%20found%20its%20way%20to%20the%20lake.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20connects%20the%20dots%20between%20the%20elevated%20levels%20of%20carbon%2C%20increased%20fire%20activity%2C%20and%20humans%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20But%20paleontologist%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnh.org%2Fresearch%2Fstaff-directory%2Fross-macphee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoss%20MacPhee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20said%20there%20isn't%20direct%20proof%20to%20make%20such%20a%20claim.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20cautious%2C%20very%20skeptical%20that%20the%20evidence%20is%20sufficient%20in%20any%20way%20to%20implicate%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20humans%20were%20starting%20fires%20in%20Southern%20California%2C%20there%20should%20be%20examples%20of%20that%20behavior%20in%20other%20areas%2C%20too.%C2%A0%26quot%3BIf%20it%20was%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20cook%20all%20the%20meat%20that%20you%20possibly%20could%20by%20starting%20these%20fires%2C%20then%20you'd%20expect%20to%20see%20the%20same%20phenomenon%20repeated%26quot%3B%20in%20places%20like%20Northern%20Canada%2C%20which%20had%20large%20numbers%20of%20megafauna%2C%20MacPhee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20lake's%20charcoal%20levels%2C%20the%20researchers%20used%20its%20sedimentary%2C%20geochemistry%2C%20and%20pollen%20data%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20region's%20temperature%20and%20precipitation.%20Based%20on%20the%20pollen%20and%20sedimentology%20records%2C%20a%20severe%20drought%20was%20affecting%20the%20area%20200%20years%20before%20the%20megafauna%20disappeared%2C%20Dunn%20said.%20Changing%20climate%20also%20played%20a%20role%20in%20their%20dwindling%20numbers%20and%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20fires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2014%2C700%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20woodland%20began%20transitioning%20into%20shrubland.%20The%20leaves%20that%20the%20camels%20and%20the%20giant%20slots%20ate%20disappeared%2C%20and%20then%20so%20did%20those%20animals.%20Grass%2C%20flowering%20plants%2C%20and%20shrubs%20cropped%20up%2C%20all%20more%20suitable%20for%20horses%20and%20other%20grazing%20animals%20than%20camels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20was%20a%20less%20tree-filled%2C%20more%20open%20landscape%20than%20before.%20Several%20studies%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.1179504%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20shown%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F987076%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincrease%20in%20wildfires%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.1214261%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emegafauna%20went%20extinct%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20certain%20regions.%20The%20loss%20of%20herbivores%20at%20La%20Brea%20could've%20contributed%20to%20a%20feedback%20loop%2C%20making%20fires%20%E2%80%94%20however%2C%20they%20started%20%E2%80%94%20more%20intense%2C%20the%20paper's%20authors%20say%3Cem%3E.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20decades-long%20debate%20among%20the%20scientific%20community%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%201960s%2C%20experts%20have%20debated%20the%20role%20of%20humans%20in%20wiping%20out%20mammoths%2C%20mastodons%2C%20and%20other%20large%20mammals%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fece3.4393%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2018%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20archaeologists%20often%20cite%20a%20combination%20of%20factors%20for%20Pleistocene%20megafaunal%20extinctions%2C%20while%20ecologists%20more%20often%20say%20humans%20were%20the%20tipping%20point%20or%20driving%20force%20behind%20it%2C%20a%20theory%20known%20as%20overkill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaelongotolist%20MacPhee%20cautions%20that%20there%20could%20be%20other%20explanations%20for%20why%20these%20animals%20in%20the%2061%2F67%20tar%20pits%20stopped%20appearing.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20entirely%20reliant%20on%20whether%20you%20have%20grounds%20for%20believing%20that%20these%20really%20are%20first%20appearances%20or%20last%20appearances%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20just%20the%20ones%20that%20you%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20find%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20was%20happening%20in%20Southern%20California%20may%20not%20have%20been%20occurring%20elsewhere%2C%20either.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20use%20conditions%20at%20one%20site%20to%20generalize%20to%20the%20entire%20continent%2C%26quot%3B%20MacPhee%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20some%20of%20the%20mammals%20that%20disappeared%20from%20Rancho%20La%20Brea%2C%20like%20wild%20horses%2C%20were%20still%20found%20in%20the%20Yukon%20until%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fcanada%2Fhamilton%2Fmammoths-and-north-american-horses-vanished-later-than-previously-thought-researchers-1.6278399%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%206%2C000%20years%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20researchers%20have%20linked%20humans'%20use%20of%20fire%20to%20an%20area's%20megafaunal%20extinction.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4539101%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2005%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20biologist%20Guy%20Robinson%20and%20his%20colleagues%20found%20an%20up-to-10-fold%20increase%20in%20charcoal%20levels%20from%2012%2C300-year-old%20sediments%20near%20Orange%20County%2C%20New%20York.%20The%20authors%20concluded%20that%20a%20combination%20of%20fire%20and%20changing%20climate%20were%20culpable%20in%20the%20local%20animals'%20demises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20tough%20sell%20for%20some%20experts%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20some%20paleontologists%20accuse%20Robinson%20of%20reading%20too%20much%20into%20ancient%20remnants%20of%20charred%20grass%2C%26quot%3B%20Sharon%20Levy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fonce-and-future-giants-9780199931163%3Fcc%3Dus%26lang%3Den%26%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20her%20book%20%26quot%3BOnce%20and%20Future%20Giants%3A%20What%20Ice%20Age%20Extinctions%20Tell%20Us%20about%20the%20Fate%20of%20Earth's%20Largest%20Animals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumans%20on%20the%20move%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20there%20was%20a%20sufficient%20number%20of%20people%20to%20do%20substantial%20damage%20to%20the%20ecosystem%20is%20MacPhee's%20question%20with%20any%20overkill%20theory.%20%26quot%3BSo%20far%2C%20it's%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20estimate%20human%20density%20many%20thousands%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20especially%20in%20North%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fanthropology.uark.edu%2Fdirectory%2F%3Fuid%3Davillase%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmelia%20Villase%C3%B1or%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20in%20the%20Univesity%20of%20Arkansas's%20anthropology%20department%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20human%20record%20in%20Southern%20California%20is%20really%20terrible%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Keefe%20said.%20The%20only%20contemporary%20fossilized%20human%20from%20the%20area%20is%20the%2013%2C0000-year-old%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fchis%2Flearn%2Fhistoryculture%2Farlington.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArlington%20Springs%20Man%3C%2Fa%3E.%20His%20co-authors%20estimate%20there%20was%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20population%20around%2013%2C200%20years%20ago%2C%20enough%20to%20have%20a%20devastating%20impact%20on%20the%20ecosystem%20with%20the%20fires%20they%20set.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ashely%20Farrell%20pulls%20a%20drawer%20filled%20with%20fossils%20in%20a%20long%20corridor%20of%20sample%20shelves%20at%20the%20paleontological%20lab%20at%20the%20George%20C.%20Page%20Museum%20at%20the%20La%20Brea%20Tar%20Pits%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ddbded4ef9f30019f8c402%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExcavation%20of%20the%20La%20Brea%20tar%20pits%20has%20yielded%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20fossils.%3Cp%3EJae%20C.%20Hong%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20agrees%20the%20loss%20of%20camels%2C%20horses%2C%20and%20megafauna%20had%20an%20effect%20on%20Southern%20California's%20environment%2013%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20Villase%C3%B1or%20said%20she%20wouldn't%20draw%20the%20same%20parallels%20the%20paper%20does%20with%20fires%20in%20the%20past%20with%20those%20affecting%20the%20region%20today.%20%26quot%3BThe%20controlled%20fires%20set%20by%20people%20%5Babout%5D%2013%2C000%20years%20ago%20and%20even%20less%20than%2010%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20at%20low%20population%20densities%2C%20are%20very%20different%20than%20the%20high%20density%2C%20fire-suppression%20caused%20fires%20of%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffires-may-have-caused-la-brea-tar-pit-extinctions-thousands-of-years-ago-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692389860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6