f%202022.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbed-bath-and-beyond-files-bankruptcy-after-running-out-options-2023-4%5C%22%3Ewell-known%20companies%20that%20have%20gone%20under%20this%20year%20include%20Bed%20Bath%20%26amp%3B%20Beyond%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20Yellow%2C%20Silicon%20Valley%20Bank%2C%20and%20Party%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20financial%20hurt%20for%20these%20companies%20has%20been%20the%20end%20of%20near-zero%20interest%20rates.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-rate-hike-july-inflation-powell-recession-federal-reserve-2023-7%5C%22%3Espike%20in%20borrowing%20costs%20has%20made%20it%20more%20difficult%20and%20cost%20prohibitive%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20struggling%20companies%20to%20raise%20debt.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20the%2010-year%20US%20Treasury%20yield%20hit%20the%20highest%20level%20since%202007.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20according%20to%20Varghese%2C%20there%20are%20three%20reasons%20why%20investors%20shouldn't%20panic%20about%20the%20recent%20uptick%20in%20bankruptcy%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1.%20The%20bond%20market%20is%20not%20concerned.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bond%20market%20would%20typically%20be%20the%20first%20to%20freak%20out%20about%20bankruptcies%20as%20failing%20companies%20that%20file%20for%20bankruptcy%20are%20often%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20defaulting%20on%20their%20debt.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20bond%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20even%20those%20who%20buy%20below-investment-grade%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20have%20not%20shown%20signs%20of%20worry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVarghese%20looked%20at%20bond%20yield%20spreads%20for%20junk%20bonds%20relative%20to%20safe%20US%20Treasurys.%20When%20the%20bond%20market%20is%20worried%20about%20bankruptcies%20and%20defaults%2C%20the%20spread%20often%20surges.%20But%20that%20the%20spread%20is%20currently%20at%203.8%25%2C%20which%20is%20in%20the%2028th%20percentile%20across%20data%20going%20back%20to%201997%2C%20and%20lower%20than%20the%20average%20spread%20of%205.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22610%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22High%20yield%20spreads%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dfa4bebd98a600197955b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22789%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarson%20Group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20current%20spread%20is%20also%20below%20what%20we%20saw%20last%20June%2C%20which%20is%20when%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20signaled%20they%20were%20going%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20more%20aggressive...%20the%20current%20level%20remains%20well%20below%20what%20we've%20seen%20ahead%20of%20prior%20crises%2C%20including%20in%202000%20and%20late%202007%2C%26quot%3B%20Varghese%20said%20in%20a%20note%20earlier%20this%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBond%20investors%20typically%20sniff%20out%20hard%20economic%20times%20for%20companies%20well%20ahead%20of%20other%20investors.%20And%20right%20now%2C%20they%20don't%20see%20any%20signs%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20Banks%20are%20not%20ringing%20the%20alarm.%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20the%20entire%20business%20model%20for%20banks%20revolves%20around%20lending%20companies%20money%20and%20then%20getting%20paid%20back%20interest%20and%20principal%2C%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20banks'%20main%20goal%20is%20to%20limit%20their%20default%20rate%20and%20avoid%20lending%20to%20companies%20that%20are%20on%20the%20road%20to%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20delinquency%20rates%20on%20business%20loans%20have%20actually%20been%20falling%2C%20not%20rising%2C%20even%20as%20bankruptcies%20tick%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22636%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Delinquency%20rates%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dfa4acb698ac0019dc872a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22753%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarson%20Group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20delinquency%20rate%20on%20business%20loans%20for%20all%20commercial%20banks%20was%20under%201%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20which%20is%20below%20the%201.1%25%20level%20seen%20just%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20Historically%2C%20business%20loan%20delinquency%20rates%20have%20averaged%20at%202.7%25%20outside%20of%20recessions%2C%20according%20to%20Varghese.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E3.%20Entrepreneurship%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20bankruptcy%20filings%20rise%2C%20so%20too%20are%20entrepreneurship%20and%20the%20formation%20of%20small%20businesses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20half%20of%20the%20year%2C%20there%20were%20more%20than%20293%2C000%20business%20applications%20that%20included%20%26quot%3Bplanned%20wages%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20indicates%20that%20the%20business%20will%20likely%20have%20a%20payroll.%20That%20number%20is%20up%202%25%20year%20over%20year%20and%20up%20more%20than%2021%25%20compared%20to%20the%20first%20half%20of%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22New%20business%20formations%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dfa4d6bd98a60019795613%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22784%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECarson%20Group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEntrepreneurship%20kicked%20into%20overdrive%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20as%20people%20ended%20up%20with%20more%20money%20in%20their%20pockets...%20applications%20jumped%20in%202020%20and%202021%20to%20an%20average%20of%20582%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20which%20was%20a%2017%25%20increase%20from%20the%20average%20we%20saw%20in%20the%20previous%20decade.%20And%20the%20good%20news%20is%20that%20we%20didn't%20see%20a%20huge%20falloff%20in%202022%20despite%20aggressive%20rate%20hikes%20by%20the%20Fed%2C%26quot%3B%20Varghese%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbankrup