%22%3A%22Unfreedom%20Monitor%3A%20India%20Finds%20Mention%20in%20New%20Report%20on%20Digital%20Authoritarianism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F09131516%2FUntitled-design-2.gif%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIndia%20is%20mentioned%20as%20a%20country%20promoting%20digital%20authoritarianism%20in%20a%20new%20report%2C%20Unfreedom%20Monitor%2C%20which%20has%20analysed%20the%20phenomenon%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Unfreedom%20Monitor%2C%20a%20project%20%E2%80%9Cto%20analyse%2C%20document%2C%20and%20report%20on%20the%20growing%20phenomenon%20of%20the%20use%20of%20digital%20communications%20technology%20to%20advance%20authoritarian%20practices%E2%80%9D%2C%20finds%20India%20mentioned%20for%20discussion%20in%20how%20digital%20authoritarianism%20is%20pushed%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%2020%20countries%20selected%20for%20examination%20in%20this%20Unfreedom%20Monitor%20are%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20type%2C%20approach%20to%20human%20rights%2C%20including%20rankings%20in%20indexes%2C%20and%20approach%20to%20the%20use%20of%20communications%20and%20surveillance%20technologies%E2%80%9D%20and%20includes%20India.%20The%20other%20countries%20are%3A%20Brazil%2C%20Cameroon%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20Egypt%2C%20El%20Salvador%2C%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20Hungary%2C%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Kenya%2C%20Kyrgyzstan%2C%20Morocco%2C%20Myanmar%2C%20Philippines%2C%20Russia%2C%20Sudan%2C%20Tanzania%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Venezuela%20and%20Zimbabwe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20is%20%E2%80%98digital%20authoritarianism%E2%80%99%20defined%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20digital%20authoritarianism%20is%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cuse%20of%20technology%20to%20advance%20repressive%20political%20interests.%E2%80%9D%20Also%20%E2%80%9Cnetworked%20authoritarianism%2C%E2%80%9D%20coined%20by%20Global%20Voices%20co-founder%20Rebecca%20MacKinnon%2C%20%E2%80%9Cemphasises%20the%20idea%20that%20people%20can%20be%20co-opted%20into%20supporting%20authoritarian%20power%20by%20participating%20in%20networked%20information%20systems%2C%20for%20example%2C%20by%20giving%20up%20their%20privacy%20in%20order%20to%20access%20services%2C%20or%20by%20using%20heavily%20censored%20discussion%20platforms%20that%20distort%20available%20information.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20%E2%80%9Cauthoritarian%20states%20do%20not%20simply%20want%20to%20restrict%20access%20to%20the%20internet%2C%20media%20and%20other%20communications%20technologies.%20Many%20states%20invest%20in%20communications%20technologies%20that%20work%20to%20curb%20freedoms.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20looks%20at%20incidents%2C%20a%20set%20of%20events%20and%20how%20governments%20have%20handled%20those%2C%20but%20mainly%2C%20for%20themes%2C%20around%20data%20governance%2C%20speech%2C%20access%20and%20information%20in%20these%20countries%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20how%20free%20and%20unfree%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20issues%20with%20Digital%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStates%20and%20government-affiliated%20bodies%20seek%20to%20control%20information%20%E2%80%9Cby%20shaping%20information%20ecosystems%2C%20running%20influence%20operations%2C%20conducting%20large-scale%20disinformation%20campaigns%2C%20and%20engaging%20in%20other%20activities%20that%20influence%20what%20people%20know%20and%20believe.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Brazil%E2%80%99s%20former%20president%20Jair%20Bolsonaro%20was%20linked%20to%20a%20government-funded%20%E2%80%9Cdigital%20militia%E2%80%9D%20that%20spread%20false%20news%20about%20COVID-19-related%20topics%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%2C%20party%20and%20followers%20find%20specific%20and%20pointed%20mention%20by%20name%20(page%2014)%2C%20%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20BJP%20party%20and%20its%20followers%20have%20long%20used%20their%20social%20media%20presence%20to%20promote%20their%20brand%20and%20troll%20religious%20and%20political%20minorities.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20absence%20of%20access%20to%20the%20internet%20and%20telecommunications%2C%20the%20report%20finds%20the%20ability%20of%20citizens%20%E2%80%9Cto%20engage%20in%20civic%20and%20political%20discourse%20is%20drastically%20reduced.%E2%80%9D%20Citing%20recent%20examples%2C%20after%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20military%20coup%2C%20the%20report%20cites%20%E2%80%9Ccitizen%20protests%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20run-up%20to%20elections%20in%20Tanzania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20%E2%80%98narrative%20frames%E2%80%99%20used%20to%20curb%20freedoms%2C%20the%20report%20finds%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpro-authoritarian%20frames%20attempt%20to%20justify%20freedom%20restrictions%20as%20being%20beneficial%20to%20citizens.%E2%80%9D%20The%20second%20most%20common%20narrative%20frame%20in%20the%20dataset%20being%20%E2%80%9Cgovernments%20must%20monitor%20media%20and%20social%20media%20to%20ensure%20political%20stability%20and%20public%20safety%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20researchers%20found%20prominently%20in%20India%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20Venezuela%2C%20Zimbabwe%2C%20Russia%2C%20Iran%2C%20Kyrgyzstan%2C%20and%20Rwanda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20%E2%80%9Cpro-authoritarian%20frame%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20finds%2C%20focusses%20on%20vilifying%20and%20dehumanising%20opponents.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20narrative%20that%20%E2%80%9Cjournalists%20who%20criticise%20the%20government%20are%20enemies%20of%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20report%20observes%20that%20this%20narrative%20has%20been%20found%20in%20India%2C%20other%20than%20Zimbabwe%2C%20Hungary%2C%20El%20Salvador%2C%20India%2C%20China%20(and%20Hong%20Kong)%2C%20Cameroon%2C%20Philippines%2C%20Rwanda%2C%20and%20Iran.%20This%20is%20linked%20to%20justifying%20%E2%80%9Cmedia%20shutdowns%2C%20arrests%20of%20journalists%2C%20justifications%20for%20surveillance%2C%20and%20restrictive%20media%20regulation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20details%20counters%20to%20government%20moves%2C%20as%20citizens%20and%20activists%20push%20back%20and%20India%20again%20finds%20mention%20here%20across%20incidents%20of%20resistance%20reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPut%20together%20by%20%E2%80%9CGlobal%20Voices%20Advox%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%20is%20the%20work%20of%20researchers%20across%20multiple%20countries.%20The%20funding%20for%20this%20project%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20Deutsche%20Welle%20Academy%20(DW).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20report%20can%20be%20read%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalvoices.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2FUnfreedom_Monitor_Observatory_Final_Report_2023.pdf%5C%22%3Ehere.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692369001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Funfreedom-monitor-india-finds-mention-in-new-report-on-digital-authoritarianism%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Twenty%20countries%20have%20been%20selected%20for%20review.%20India%E2%80%99s%20PM%2C%20ruling%20party%20and%20its%20%E2%80%98followers%E2%80%99%20are%20named%20with%20Brazil%E2%80%99s%20former%20President%20Jair%20Bolsonaro%20when%20discussing%20%E2%80%98states%20and%20government-affiliated%20bodies%20seeking%20to%20control%20information.%E2%80%99%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Funfreedom-monitor-india-finds-mention-in-new-report-on-digital-authoritarianism%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Malaika%20Arora's%20exotic%20vacation%20pics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692369000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102828272%2Cimgsize-91198.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fmalaika-aroras-exotic-vacation-pics