irst.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20the%20actual%20G-20%20summit%20in%20September%2C%20one%20of%20the%20other%20important%20spotlights%20from%20the%20Indian%20perspective%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20host%2C%20Modi%2C%20with%20Xi.%20It%20appears%20that%20a%20substantive%20meeting%2C%20their%20first%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20border%20stand-off%20in%20May%202020%2C%20may%20happen%20sooner%20than%20that%2C%20if%20things%20pan%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20learnt%20that%20there%20is%20certainly%20interest%20in%20India%20for%20a%20meeting%20to%20take%20place%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20in%20South%20Africa.%20However%2C%20informed%20sources%20say%20the%20pressing%20issue%20now%20revolves%20around%20customary%20protocol%20%E2%80%93%20specifically%20in%20determining%20which%20side%20will%20initiate%20the%20formal%20request%20for%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20relations%20have%20gone%20into%20a%20deep%20freeze%20since%20May%202020%2C%20there%20has%20been%20several%20rounds%20of%20military%20and%20diplomatic%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20which%20eventually%20led%20to%20disengagement%20at%20certain%20friction%20points.%20And%20yet%20there%20has%20been%20no%20further%20progress%20on%20the%20remaining%20points%20of%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok%20for%20two%20years%2C%20which%20renders%20the%20situation%20ripe%20for%20political%20intervention.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20already%20been%20strong%20indication%20for%20some%20weeks%20that%20positive%20atmospherics%20were%20being%20created%20for%20a%20possible%20bilateral%20meeting%20between%20the%20two%20leaders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37010%2FJoint%2BPress%2BRelease%2Bof%2Bthe%2B19th%2BRound%2Bof%2BIndiaChina%2BCorps%2BCommander%2BLevel%2BMeeting%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ejoint%20press%20release%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20issued%20earlier%20this%20week%20had%20signalled%20this%20mood.%20Ranging%20from%20%E2%80%9Cpositive%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cforward-looking%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20common%20readout%20of%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20Corp%20commanders%E2%80%99%20meeting%20last%20weekend%20had%20a%20high%20concentration%20of%20optimistic-sounding%20descriptors%20about%20the%20discussions%20on%20the%20continuing%20stand-off%20at%20eastern%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20have%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Feng.chinamil.com.cn%2FCHINA_209163%2FTopStories_209189%2F10207209.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eother%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F35496%2FJoint%2BPress%2BRelease%2Bof%2Bthe%2B16th%2BRound%2Bof%2BIndiaChina%2BCorps%2BCommander%2BLevel%2BMeeting%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ejoint%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetailm.aspx%3FPRID%3D1789701%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epress%20releases%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20after%20military%20talks%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20However%2C%20even%20those%20releases%20did%20not%20contain%20as%20many%20affirmative%20words%20and%20phrases%20as%20there%20were%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20document.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20leadership%20meeting%20still%20not%20finalised%2C%20there%20is%20always%20uncertainty%20about%20whether%20it%20will%20take%20place%20till%20the%20minute.%20There%20had%20been%20similar%20buzz%20about%20a%20Modi-Xi%20meeting%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20SCO%20summit%20in%20Samarkand%20last%20year.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wionews.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-china-disengagement-at-gogra-hotsprings-pp15-raise-hope-of-modi-xi-meet-at-sco-samarkand-summit-514177%5C%22%3EThat%20speculation%20had%20been%20fueled%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20completion%20of%20disengagement%20at%20Gogra-Hot%20Springs%20in%20mid-July%202022.%20Nonetheless%2C%20no%20meeting%20between%20Xi%20and%20Modi%20transpired%20in%20Uzbekistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20the%20weightage%20attributed%20to%20the%20conjecture%20regarding%20a%20potential%20bilateral%20meeting%20in%20South%20Africa%20is%20also%20linked%20to%20the%20upcoming%20G-20%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20would%20also%20certainly%20China%E2%80%99s%20support%20to%20get%20the%20maximum%20bang%20for%20the%20buck%20out%20of%20the%20Delhi%20declaration%20of%20the%20G-20%20summit.%20While%20the%20Ukraine%20issue%20will%20continue%20to%20see%20dissension%20from%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20India%20would%20require%20China%20to%20not%20put%20a%20spanner%20in%20the%20work%20for%20a%20range%20of%20other%20subjects%20that%20are%20priority%20policies%20for%20the%20Indian%20PM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20China%20has%20been%20regularly%20objecting%20on%20including%20any%20reference%20to%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20pet%20concepts%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mygov.in%2Flife%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520this%2520context%252C%2520the%2520concept%2Ctowards%2520%25E2%2580%259Cmindful%2520and%2520deliberate%2520utilisation%252C%5C%22%3ELiFe%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1908120%5C%22%3Epromotion%20of%20millets%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20main%20outcome%20document%20at%20the%20ministerial%20meetings.%20India%20has%2C%20of%20course%2C%20also%20blocked%20any%20mention%20of%20tell-tale%20phrases%20e%20reflecting%20%E2%80%98Xi%20Jinping%20Thought%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20well%20as%2C%20pet%20projects%20like%20Gl%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmprc.gov.cn%2Feng%2Fwjb_663304%2Fwjbz_663308%2F2461_663310%2F202209%2Ft20220922_10769721.html%5C%22%3Eobal%20Development%20Initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dxi%2Bjinping%2Bglobal%2Bseurity%2Binvitiative%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Security%20Initiative%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Indian%20officials%20are%20not%20holding%20their%20breath%20on%20finding%20a%20consensus%20over%20language%20regarding%20Ukraine%20in%20the%20G-20%20final%20declaration%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20cooperation%20remains%20essential%20to%20enable%20New%20Delhi%20to%20assert%20that%20there%20was%20unanimous%20backing%20for%20the%20predominant%20portion%20of%20the%20outcome%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%C2%A0%3Cspan%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20top%20diplomat%20Wang%20Yi%20had%20already%20held%20two%20rounds%20of%20meeting%20with%20Indian%20interlocutors%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20and%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20Doval-Wang%20meeting%2C%20the%20Chinese%20readout%20stated%20that%20there%20had%20been%20exchange%20of%20remarks%20between%20the%20top%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20leaders%20at%20the%20G-20%20dinner%20summit%20in%20Bali.%20It%20was%20a%20previously%20unreported%20conversation%2C%20with%20the%20Indian%20side%20having%20only%20mentioned%20that%20there%20was%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F35898%2FTranscript_of_Special_Briefing_by_Foreign_Secretary_on_the_Visit_of_the_Prime_Minister_to_Indonesia_for_G20_Summit_November_16_2022%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexchange%20of%20courtesies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Indian%20media%20asked%20for%20clarification%2C%20New%20Delhi%20did%20not%20dismiss%20the%20Chinese%20version%2C%20but%20rather%20seemed%20to%20endorse%20it%20to%20an%20extent.%20This%20was%20a%20surprise%20to%20most%20observers%20who%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20MEA%E2%80%99s%20usual%20template%20of%20available%20replies.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Feight-months-later-india-says-modi-xi-did-talk-about-stabilising-ties-at-bali-encounter%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20spokesperson%E2%80%99s%20implicit%20acknowledgment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20complete%20details%20had%20not%20been%20furnished%20eight%20months%20earlier%20came%20as%20a%20surprise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENext%20week%2C%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20bloc%20of%20five%20emerging%20economies%20will%20be%20meeting%20physically%20for%20their%20first%20summit%20since%202019.%20While%20the%20Russian%20president%20Vladimir%20Putin%20will%20not%20attend%20due%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-cpi.int%2Fnews%2Fsituation-ukraine-icc-judges-issue-arrest-warrants-against-vladimir-vladimirovich-putin-and%5C%22%3EInternational%20Criminal%20Court%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20warrant%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20confirmed%20today%2C%20August%2018%2C%20that%20Xi%20Jinping%20would%20travel%20to%20South%20Africa%20for%20a%20four-day%20visit.%20The%20foreign%20trip%2C%20from%20April%2021%20to%2024%2C%20is%20relatively%20long%20by%20Chinese%20standards%20and%20is%20going%20to%20include%20both%20a%20BRICS%20summit%20and%20a%20bilateral%20state%20visit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20current%20schedule%2C%20Modi%20and%20his%20entourage%20will%20reach%20South%20Africa%20on%20August%2022%2C%20in%20the%20evening%20according%20to%20local%20time.%20He%20will%20attend%20the%20informal%20meet%20for%20participating%20leaders%20after%20arrival.%20The%20main%20BRICS%20summit%20will%20be%20held%20on%20August%2023%2C%20with%20the%20next%20day%20reserved%20for%20the%20BRICS%20outreach%20sessions.%20The%20Indian%20PM%20will%20depart%20for%20New%20Delhi%20on%20Thursday%20evening.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20South%20Africa%20has%20invited%20many%20African%20leaders%20as%20special%20invitees%2C%20it%20is%20understood%20there%20is%20enough%20time%20in%20the%20schedule%20for%20the%20Indian%20PM%20to%20have%20a%20substantive%20bilateral%20meeting%20with%20the%20Chinese%20leader.%20As%20usual%2C%20the%20dilemma%20%E2%80%93%20a%20common%20one%20for%20Indian%20diplomats%20faced%20with%20a%20potential%20meeting%20with%20Chinese%20or%20Pakistani%20leadership%20%E2%80%93%20centres%20on%20who%20makes%20the%20first%20request.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692362735000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18181342%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-6.09.53.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnarendra-modi-xi-jinping-india-china-south-africa%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20joint%20India-China%20press%20release%20issued%20earlier%20this%20week%20had%20signalled%20that%20there%20may%20be%20a%20mood%20to%20make%20such%20a%20meeting%20happen.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnarendra-modi-xi-jinping-india-china-south-africa%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20ABVP%20to%20Challenging%20Modi%3A%20The%20Story%20of%20Ajay%20Rai%2C%20the%20New%20UP%20Congress%26nbsp%3BPresident%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18143550%2FCskSyTUewoLSCNek.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Ajay%20Rai%20%E2%80%93%20a%20politician%20who%20started%20his%20career%20with%20the%20student%20wing%20of%20Hindu%20nationalist%20outfit%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20before%20going%20on%20to%20contest%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20against%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Varanasi%20%E2%80%93%20was%20nominated%20by%20the%20Congress%20as%20its%20state%20president%20in%20politically-significant%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20on%20Thursday%2C%20August%2017.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERai%20is%20a%20former%20five-time%20MLA%20from%20Varanasi.%20He%20replaced%20Brij%20Lal%20Khabri%2C%20who%20had%20been%20appointed%20as%20the%20Congress%20state%20head%20less%20than%20a%20year%20ago%20in%20what%20was%20then%20seen%20as%20a%20move%20by%20the%20party%20to%20reignite%20interest%20among%20the%20numerically-important%20Dalit%20voters%20accounting%20for%2021.5%25%20of%20the%20state%20population.%20While%20Khabri%20is%20a%20Dalit%2C%20Rai%2C%2054%2C%20belongs%20to%20the%20dominant%20upper%20caste%20Bhumihar%20community%2C%20which%20though%20inconsequential%20in%20the%20overall%20caste%20arithmetic%20of%20UP%2C%20has%20political%20weight%20in%20districts%20around%20Varanasi%20and%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98jati%20asmita%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20caste%20pride.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20a%20Congress%20source%20said%20that%20Rai%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20nominated%20to%20the%20post%20due%20to%20his%20personal%20record%20and%20influence%2C%20rather%20than%20just%20caste%20calculations.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20already%20have%20a%20Dalit%20(Mallikarjun%20Kharge)%20as%20the%20national%20president.%20In%20UP%20we%20want%20someone%20who%20can%20fight%20on%20the%20streets.%20We%20have%20picked%20someone%20who%20fought%20directly%20against%20Modi.%20We%20want%20to%20indicate%20that%20our%20fight%20is%20directly%20against%20the%20BJP%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Congress%20source.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20Khabri%2C%20Rai%20was%20also%20an%20import%20into%20the%20Congress.%20Khabri%20was%20a%20former%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20MP%20from%20Jalaun.%20Rai%20had%20a%20long%20past%20with%20the%20BJP%20before%20he%20joined%20the%20Congress.%20He%20was%20last%20year%20appointed%20a%20provincial%20president%20of%20the%20party%20in%20East%20UP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20graduate%20of%20the%20Kashi%20Vidyapeeth%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20Rai%20began%20his%20career%20as%20a%20convenor%20of%20the%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Vidyarthi%20Parishad%20(ABVP)%2C%20the%20student%20wing%20of%20the%20RSS-BJP%2C%20in%201991-92.%20Rai%20participated%20in%20the%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20movement%20and%20was%20even%20held%20in%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20jail%20under%20preventive%20sections%20of%20the%20law.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20entered%20electoral%20politics%20with%20a%20bang%20in%201996%20when%20he%20defeated%20nine-time%20sitting%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20MLA%20Udal%20from%20the%20Kolasla%20seat.%20In%202002%2C%20he%20won%20from%20the%20Kolasla%20assembly%20constituency%20again.%20A%20few%20months%20later%20he%20was%20rewarded%20with%20a%20ministerial%20berth%20as%20state%20minister%20for%20cooperatives%20in%20the%20Mayawati-led%20BSP-BJP%20alliance%20government.%20After%20a%20third%20assembly%20win%20in%202007%2C%20feeling%20betrayed%20that%20the%20party%20had%20picked%20veteran%20leader%20Murli%20Manohar%20Joshi%20as%20its%20Lok%20Sabha%20candidate%20from%20Varanasi%20despite%20promising%20it%20to%20him%2C%20he%20quit%20the%20BJP%20in%202009.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20promised%20the%20ticket%20and%20I%20worked%20hard%20for%20a%20year.%20But%20for%20reasons%20unknown%20I%20was%20shunted%20at%20the%20last%20moment%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20me%20in%202014.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERai%20contested%20the%202009%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20as%20a%20candidate%20of%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party.%20He%20stood%20third%20with%201.23%20lakh%20votes%20but%20the%20contest%20would%20be%20remembered%20more%20for%20the%20way%20tainted%20politician%20and%20rival%20Bahubali%20of%20Purvanchal%20Mukhtar%20Ansari%20gave%20Joshi%20a%20run%20for%20his%20money.%20Ansari%20lost%20to%20Joshi%20by%20a%20relatively%20thin%20margin%20of%2017%2C000%20votes%20in%20what%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20communally%20polarised%20contest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20Rai%20denies%20it%2C%20in%20the%20narrow%20lanes%20and%20by-lanes%20of%20Varanasi%2C%20it%20is%20often%20said%20that%20after%20sensing%20that%20he%20would%20not%20win%2C%20Rai%20campaigned%20for%20Joshi%20to%20ensure%20Mukhtar%20Ansari%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20because%20of%20their%20bitter%20relationship.%20In%20June%202023%2C%20a%20Varanasi%20court%20convicted%20Ansari%20and%20sentenced%20him%20to%20life%20for%20murdering%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20brother%20Awadesh%20Rai%20in%201991.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERai%E2%80%99s%20journey%20with%20the%20Congress%20started%20in%202012%20when%20he%20contested%20as%20its%20candidate%20and%20routed%20the%20BJP%20nominee%20to%20secure%20Pindra%20(earlier%20known%20as%20Kolasla).%20The%20BJP%20candidate%20was%20reduced%20to%203%2C000%20votes%20as%20Rai%20got%20his%20sweet%20revenge.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20in%20this%20setting%20that%20the%20Congress%20in%202014%2C%20looking%20to%20prevent%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministerial%20face%20Narendra%20Modi%20from%20securing%20Varanasi%2C%20one%20of%20the%20holiest%20Hindu%20cities%2C%20picked%20Rai%20as%20his%20challenger.%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20was%20the%20other%20candidate%20in%20the%20highly-watched%20contest.%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20nomination%20elevated%20his%20stature.%20However%2C%20since%20the%20contest%20was%20reduced%20to%20a%20fight%20between%20Modi%20and%20Kejriwal%2C%20he%20had%20to%20contend%20with%20a%20third-place%20finish.%20The%20same%20thing%20happened%20in%202019%20when%20the%20SP-BSP%20alliance%20candidate%20o%20edged%20past%20him%20as%20runner-up%20against%20Modi%2C%20who%20won%20by%20a%20huge%20margin.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%202014%20and%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20results%20in%20Varanasi%20may%20not%20be%20a%20referendum%20on%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20local%20popularity%2C%20his%20electoral%20fortunes%20have%20definitely%20declined%20ever%20since%20his%20association%20with%20the%20grand%20old%20party.%20In%20both%202017%20and%202022%2C%20Rai%20stood%20third%20from%20Pindra%2C%20a%20seat%20he%20had%20once%20claimed%20as%20his%20own.%20A%20big%20question%20mark%20also%20hangs%20on%20how%20Rai%20will%20rejuvenate%20the%20debilitated%20Congress%20unit%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20as%20we%20inch%20closer%20to%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692361818000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18143550%2FCskSyTUewoLSCNek.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffrom-abvp-to-challenging-modi-the-story-of-ajay-rai-the-new-up-congress-president%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rai%E2%80%99s%20journey%20with%20the%20Congress%20started%20in%202012%20when%20he%20contested%20as%20its%20candidate%20and%20routed%C2%A0the%20BJP%20nominee%20to%20secure%20the%20Pindra%20seat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffrom-abvp-to-challenging-modi-the-story-of-ajay-rai-the-new-up-congress-president%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ambedkar%20University%20Faculty%20Group%20Raises%20Concerns%20Over%20Unhealthy%20Environment%2C%20Poor%20Infra%2C%20Harassment%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F03145909%2Fimage-2021-07-03T145902.775.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Worsening%20work%20environment%2C%20targeted%20harassment%2C%20erosion%20of%20a%20culture%20of%20dialogue%2C%20stagnant%20careers%2C%20and%20shabby%20infrastructure%20are%20some%20of%20the%20concerns%20raised%20by%20the%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20University%20Delhi%20Faculty%20Association%20(AUDFA)%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20dated%20August%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaising%20the%20concern%20of%20a%20considerable%20decline%20in%20the%20number%20of%20applications%2C%20the%20AUDFA%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CSince%202020%2C%20applications%20to%20AUD%E2%80%99s%20UG%20and%20PG%20programmes%20have%20shrunk%20alarmingly.%20Interdisciplinary%20PG%20programmes%20that%20consistently%20received%20over%20400%20applications%20now%20receive%20a%20few%20dozen%20applications.%20Even%20the%20most%20popular%20programmes%20have%20seen%20reduced%20numbers%20of%20applicants.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20externally%20funded%20projects%20have%20dried%20up.%20%E2%80%9CAUD%20faculty%20and%20Centres%20regularly%20undertook%20projects%20and%20consultancies%20worth%20around%20Rs%205-7%20crores%20a%20year.%20This%20number%20barely%20reaches%20Rs%201%20crore%20today.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202020%2C%20more%20than%2015%20faculty%20members%2C%20including%20seasoned%20academics%2C%20have%20resigned%20from%20the%20university.%20Some%20have%20transitioned%20to%20private%20institutions%2C%20while%20others%20have%20departed%20from%20AUD%20without%20securing%20new%20positions%20due%20to%20the%20existing%20challenging%20work%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaculty%20members%20regularly%20face%20obstacles%20such%20as%20denied%20NOCs%20(no-objection%20certificates)%20for%20academic%20engagements%2C%20visa%20issues%2C%20and%20delayed%20approvals%20for%20academic%20positions.%20Cumbersome%20procedures%20for%20external%20projects%20are%20causing%20some%20faculty%20to%20abandon%20research%20opportunities%20to%20avoid%20red%20tape%20in%20applying%20for%20and%20carrying%20out%20external%20grants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20posts%20of%20visiting%20faculty%20on%20contract%20(in%20lieu%20of%20regular%20faculty)%20have%20been%20disbanded%20in%20favour%20of%20guest%20faculty%2C%20leading%20to%20poorer%20remuneration%20for%20the%20concerned%20faculty%20and%20gaps%20in%20faculty%20support%20for%20programmes%20to%20run%20optimally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFaculty%20is%20harassed%20by%20the%20administration%20on%20different%20grounds.%20There%20is%20a%20running%20thread%20of%20purposeful%20regressive%20reinterpretation%20of%20decisions%20taken%20by%20the%20administration%20and%2For%20committees%20in%20the%20past.%20This%20leads%20to%20faculty%20being%20subjected%20to%20punitive%20action%20for%20no%20fault%20of%20theirs.%20Some%20of%20these%20actions%20have%20resulted%20in%20a%20sudden%20financial%20burden%20to%20the%20concerned%20faculty%20members%2C%20apart%20from%20loss%20of%20service%20and%20mental%20stress%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPointing%20out%20the%20erosion%20of%20a%20culture%20of%20dialogue%20in%20the%20university%2C%20it%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CCritical%20decisions%20that%20have%20long-term%20consequences%20for%20the%20university%20are%20not%20discussed%20with%20many%20of%20the%20stakeholders.%20Consultative%20and%20constructive%20review%20processes%20that%20were%20the%20norm%20have%20been%20abandoned.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18155821%2Fimage-1233.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18155821%2Fimage-1233.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18155821%2Fimage-1233-300x132.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18155821%2Fimage-1233-1024x451.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668606%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22529%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EShabby%20infrastructure%20at%20Ambedkar%20University.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAUD%20campuses%20suffer%20from%20dilapidated%2C%20unsanitary%2C%20and%20unsafe%20infrastructure.%20Students%20and%20faculty%20routinely%20work%20with%20broken%20furniture%2C%20power%20outages%2C%20non-%20functioning%20air%20conditioner