ef%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fnews-updates%2Fdelhi-court-delhi-riots-delhi-police-manipulating-evidence-chargesheets-predetermined-manner-discharges-235493%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20court%20found%20inconsistencies%20in%20the%20chargesheets%20and%20subsequent%20statements%2C%20suggesting%20an%20attempt%20to%20cover%20up%20flaws%20in%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20case.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR%2071%2F2020)%20was%20registered%20at%20Dayalpur%20police%20station%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20rukka%20prepared%20by%20an%20Assistant%20Sub-Inspector%20on%20February%2028%2C%202020.%20(Rukka%20is%20just%20a%20complaint%20copy%20from%20which%20the%20contents%20are%20taken%20for%20filing%20FIRs.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20the%20Investigating%20Officer%20clubbed%20several%20complaints%20made%20by%20Farooq%20Ahmad%2C%20Shahbaz%20Malik%2C%20Nadeem%20Farooq%20and%20Jai%20Shankar%20Sharma%20in%20the%20case%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20chargesheet%20was%20filed%20against%20the%20three%20persons%20on%20July%2014%2C%202020%2C%20and%20cognisance%20of%20the%20same%20was%20taken%20on%20December%209%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20two%20supplementary%20chargesheets%20were%20filed%20on%20February%2015%2C%202022%2C%20and%20February%2016%20this%20year%2C%20along%20with%20certain%20documents%20and%20fresh%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpolice-witness-not-credible-callous-probe-how-the-delhi-riots-cases-have-evolved%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Police%20Witness%20Not%20Credible%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Callous%20Probe%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Delhi%20Riots%20Cases%20Have%20Evolved%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20noted%20that%20in%20the%20first%20supplementary%20chargesheet%2C%20the%20investigating%20officer%20(IO)%20included%20three%20individuals%20as%20accused%20who%20were%20not%20mentioned%20in%20a%20constable%E2%80%99s%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20highlighted%20that%20until%20the%20court%20began%20questioning%20the%20timeline%20of%20events%20mentioned%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20IO%20consistently%20maintained%20in%20both%20the%20main%20and%20the%20first%20supplementary%20chargesheets%20that%2C%20except%20for%20one%20incident%2C%20all%20other%20reported%20incidents%20by%20various%20complainants%20occurred%20during%20the%20night%20between%20February%2024%20and%2025%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20further%20noticed%20that%20when%20the%20complaints%20were%20clubbed%20together%2C%20there%20was%20no%20record%20of%20the%20police%20being%20informed%20that%20the%20same%20group%20had%20been%20involved%20in%20acts%20of%20vandalism%20and%20arson%20from%20the%20night%20before%20until%20the%20information%20was%20recorded%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20February%2025%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20the%20subsequent%20statements%20from%20the%20complainants%20were%20documented%20primarily%20to%20hide%20the%20gaps%20in%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20case%20and%20to%20provide%20a%20basis%20for%20charging%20the%20accused%20individuals.%20The%20court%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20investigating%20officer%20failed%20to%20present%20any%20evidence%20demonstrating%20the%20accuracy%20of%20these%20subsequent%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692351035000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F14122931%2FDelhi-riots.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-riots-court-discharges-3-men-raises-suspicion-of-manipulated-evidence-by-police%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20judge%20has%20referred%20the%20matter%20back%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20for%20an%20assessment%20of%20the%20investigation%20and%20to%20bring%20the%20complaints%20to%20a%20legal%20and%20logical%20end.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-riots-court-discharges-3-men-raises-suspicion-of-manipulated-evidence-by-police%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jio%20Financial%20Services%20set%20to%20be%20listed%20on%20stock%20exchanges%20on%20August%2021%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692350771000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-04%2F26%2Ffull%2F1682473178-3914.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fjio-financial-services-set-to-be-listed-on-stock-exchanges-on-august-21-123081800389_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BSE%20said%20the%20scrip%20would%20be%20in%20the%20Trade-for-Trade%20segment%20for%2010%20trading%20days%20and%20will%20trade%20from%20this%20Monday%20with%20the%20symbol%20of%20JIOFIN%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fjio-financial-services-set-to-be-listed-on-stock-exchanges-on-august-21-123081800389_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Few%20Functional%20Khadi%20Units%2C%20Tea%20Board%20Graft%2C%20Unapproved%20Spending%3A%20Inside%20the%20CAG%20Reports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18114050%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20reports%20presented%20to%20parliament%20during%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%20that%20ended%20last%20week%20have%20found%20irregularities%20in%20the%20working%20of%20Khadi%20units%2C%20poor%20monitoring%20by%20the%20Tea%20Board%2C%20and%20non-approved%20sanctioning%20of%20funds%20for%20the%20Swadesh%20Darshan%20scheme%2C%20along%20with%20poor%20estate%20management%20by%20the%20Bharat%20Sanchar%20Nigam%20Limited.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20part%20two%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-nhai-toll-collection-railway-bharatmala-udan%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eseries%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20all%2012%20CAG%20reports%20presented%20in%20parliament%2C%20we%20look%20at%20findings%20from%20four%20reports%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EMinistry%20of%20MSME%3A%20Compliance%20Audit%20on%20%E2%80%9CDepartmental%20Trading%20Units%20including%20Supply%20Chain%20Management%20in%20Khadi%20and%20Village%20Industries%20Commission%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EPerformance%20Audit%20on%20%E2%80%9CSwadesh%20Darshan%20Scheme%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Union%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Tourism%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EPerformance%20Audit%20on%20%E2%80%9CRole%20of%20Tea%20Board%20of%20India%20in%20Development%20of%20Tea%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Union%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20Commerce%20and%20Industry%2C%20and%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3ECompliance%20Audit%20on%20Finance%20and%20Communication%2C%20Union%20Government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELess%20than%2020%25%20khadi%20units%20working%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119137%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Departmental%20Trading%20Units%20Including%20Supply%20Chain%20Management%20in%20Khadi%20and%20Village%20Industries%20Commission%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Micro%2C%20Small%20and%20Medium%20Enterprises%20(MSME)%20has%20found%20that%20less%20than%2020%25%20of%20departmental%20trading%20units%20were%20operational.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Khadi%20and%20Village%20Industries%20Commission%20(KVIC)%20was%20formed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20under%20the%20Khadi%20and%20Village%20Industries%20Commission%20Act%20of%201956%20to%20plan%2C%20promote%2C%20facilitate%2C%20organise%20and%20assist%20in%20the%20establishment%20and%20development%20of%20Khadi%20and%20village%20industries%20in%20rural%20areas%20in%20coordination%20with%20other%20agencies%20engaged%20in%20rural%20development%20wherever%20necessary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20departmental%20trading%20units%20were%20established%20by%20KVIC%20to%20carry%20out%20production%20and%20sales%20activities%20of%20Khadi%20and%20village%20industries%20products.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20report%20is%20based%20on%20an%20audit%20conducted%20for%20the%20period%20from%202017-18%20to%202020-21.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CKVIC%20had%20established%2092%20Departmental%20Trading%20Units%20over%20the%20years.%20Of%20these%2C%20only%2018%20Departmental%20Trading%20Units%20were%20functional%20as%20on%2031%20March%202021%20and%2074%20Departmental%20Trading%20Units%20have%20become%20defunct%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time%20(73%20Departmental%20Trading%20Units%20became%20defunct%20during%20the%20period%201962-2016%20and%20one%20Departmental%20Trading%20Unit%20was%20closed%20in%202019)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20only%20less%20than%2020%25%20of%20departmental%20trading%20units%20were%20able%20to%20continue%20operations%2C%20%E2%80%9CKVIC%20has%20not%20done%20any%20analysis%20to%20identify%20the%20reasons%E2%80%9D%20behind%20them%20becoming%20defunct.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20reason%20for%20closure%20was%20not%20available%20for%2011%20out%20of%2025%20departmental%20trading%20units.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20case%20of%20three%20departmental%20trading%20units%2C%20the%20reasons%20and%20justifications%20of%20closure%20were%20not%20fully%20convincing%20and%20more%20efforts%20by%20KVIC%20could%20have%20prevented%20their%20closure%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20case%20of%20another%20two%20departmental%20trading%20units%2C%20private%20parties%20were%20generating%20considerable%20revenue%20through%20unauthorised%20sales%20of%20Khadi%20products%20indicating%20scope%20for%20revenue%20generation%20through%20these%20departmental%20trading%20units.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%20the%20Khadi%20Gramodyog%20Bhavans%20of%20KVIC%20were%20collecting%20excess%20share%20of%20production%20subsidy%20due%20from%20the%20Khadi%20Institutions%20whose%20products%20were%20being%20sold%20through%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20marking%20the%208th%20National%20Handloom%20Day%20on%20August%207%2C%20prime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20demand%20for%20Khadi%20clothes%20is%20increasing%20in%20India%20and%20abroad%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1688456609008128002%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%20the%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20report%20has%20found%20KVIC%20was%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%98unable%20to%20fulfil%20the%20demand%20in%20respect%20of%20wholesale%2FGovernment%20requirements%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20suppliers%E2%80%9D%20and%20has%20recommended%20that%20KVIC%20take%20effective%20action%20to%20%E2%80%9Caugment%20the%20capacity%20of%20existing%20suppliers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20recommended%20inducting%20more%20suppliers%20to%20increase%20the%20capacity%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20demand%20in%20the%20Government%20sector.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMinistry%20of%20Tourism%20sanctioned%20funds%20for%20Swadesh%20Darshan%20scheme%20without%20Cabinet%20approval%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20performance%20audit%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119135%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESwadesh%20Darshan%20Scheme%20implemented%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Tourism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20conducted%20from%20the%20period%20from%20the%20Scheme%E2%80%99s%20inception%20in%20January%202015%20to%20March%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20while%20the%20scheme%20was%20launched%20with%20an%20initial%20outlay%20of%20Rs%20500%20crore%2C%20the%20Ministry%20continued%20to%20sanction%20projects%20and%20the%20amount%20sanctioned%20had%20exceeded%20Rs%204%2C000%20crore%20by%202016-17.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20funds%20were%20sanctioned%20by%20the%20ministry%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20obtaining%20approval%20of%20the%20Cabinet%2C%20which%20was%20necessary%20for%20sanctioning%20projects%20costing%20above%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20the%20scheme%20was%20implemented%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20conducting%20any%20feasibility%20study.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20ministry%20identified%2015%20tourist%20circuits%20for%20development%20under%20the%20scheme%20and%20a%20total%20of%2076%20projects%20were%20sanctioned%20under%20the%20scheme%20since%20its%20inception.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNon-preparation%20of%20the%20feasibility%20report%20resulted%20in%20poor%20identification%20of%20sites%20and%20deficiencies%20in%20execution%20of%20projects%2C%20such%20as%20delay%20in%20completion%20of%20the%20projects%20and%20non-utilisation%20of%20funds%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20rural%20circuit%20did%20not%20receive%20adequate%20attention%20from%20the%20ministry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18115732%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-11.51.5.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18115732%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-11.51.5.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18115732%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-11.51.5-300x200.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18115732%2FScreenshot-2023-08-18-at-11.51.5-1024x681.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668547%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22798%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20report%20said%20that%20the%20ministry%20identified%2015%20tourist%20circuits%20for%20development%20under%20the%20scheme%20and%20a%20total%20of%2076%20projects%20were%20sanctioned%20under%20the%20scheme%20since%20its%20inception.%E2%80%99%20Photo%3A%20dilip%E2%80%A6%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY-NC-ND%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20on%2031%20March%202022%2C%20the%20total%20expenditure%20incurred%20under%20rural%20circuit%20was%20only%20Rs%2030.84%20crore%2C%20which%20constituted%20only%200.73%25%20of%20the%20total%20expenditure%20incurred%20under%20the%20Scheme.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%20the%20ministry%20did%20not%20develop%20a%20formal%20mechanism%20for%20evaluation%20and%20approval%20of%20projects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%2018%20months%20to%2036%20months%20had%20been%20given%20to%20the%20State%20Governments%2FUTs%20to%20complete%20the%20projects%2C%20the%20Ministry%20itself%20kept%20the%20project%20proposals%20pending%20for%20up%20to%20six%20years%20in%20few%20cases%20without%20any%20action%20as%20it%20did%20not%20have%20a%20defined%20timeline%20for%20approval%20or%20rejection%20of%20project%20proposals%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20also%20found%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lack%20of%20%E2%80%9Cproper%20planning%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20Ministry%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20did%20not%20ensure%20the%20preparation%20of%20a%20national%20or%20state-level%20plan%20before%20launching%20the%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20after%20the%20scheme%20was%20launched%2C%20it%20did%20not%20ensure%20preparation%20of%20detailed%20perspective%20plans%20for%2014%20out%20of%2015%20tourist%20circuits%2Fthemes%2C%20which%20were%20to%20form%20the%20basis%20of%20selection%20of%20projects%20and%20preparation%20of%20detailed%20project%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20the%20Ministry%20did%20not%20have%20any%20long-term%20vision%2Fpolicy%20for%20implementing%20the%20Scheme%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Poor%E2%80%99%20monitoring%2C%20ineligible%20subsidy%20payments%20by%20Tea%20Board%20indicate%20%E2%80%98corruption%2Ffraud%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20report%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119134%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERole%20of%20Tea%20Board%20India%20in%20development%20of%20tea%20in%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20recommended%20that%20the%20Tea%20Board%20initiate%20steps%20to%20investigate%20the%20cases%20of%20ineligible%20subsidy%20payments%20as%20these%20indicate%20%E2%80%9Ccorruption%2F%20fraud%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Tea%20Board%20was%20authorised%20by%20the%20Tea%20Act%2C%201953%20to%20inspect%20the%20quality%20of%20tea.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20on%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Tea%20Board%20was%20conducted%20during%20November%202021%20and%20April%202022%20covering%20the%20period%20from%202016-17%20to%202020-21.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20recommended%20that%20Tea%20Board%20should%20earmark%20stipulated%20budgetary%20allocation%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fbudget2016-2017%2Fub2016-17%2Feb%2Fstat21.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EScheduled%20Caste%20Sub%20Plan%20and%20Tribal%20Area%20Sub%20Plan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E-intended%20to%20channel%20the%20flow%20of%20resources%20from%20the%20general%20sectors%20in%20the%20Central%20Ministries%2F%20Departments%20towards%20the%20development%20of%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%2C%20at%20least%20in%20proportion%20to%20their%20numbers%20in%20the%20population%2C%20both%20in%20physical%20and%20financial%20terms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CPlanning%20Commission%2F%20NITI%20Aayog%20directives%20provide%20for%20mandatory%20allocation%20of%20funds%20as%204.5%25%20for%20Scheduled%20Caste%20Sub%20Plan%20during%202016-17%20which%20was%20increased%20to%208.3%25%20from%202017-18%20onwards.%20However%2C%20Tea%20Board%20allocated%20only%203.29%20per%20cent%20for%20Scheduled%20Caste%20Sub%20Plan%20scheme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20allocation%20towards%20Tribal%20Area%20Sub%20Plan%20scheme%20was%20only%202.63%20per%20cent%20against%20mandatory%20allocation%20of%204.3%20per%20cent%20during%202018-19%20to%202020-21%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20in%20Assam%2C%20the%20Golaghat%20Regional%20Office%20under%20Guwahati%20Zonal%20Office%20of%20Tea%20Board%20disbursed%20subsidies%20under%20Scheduled%20Caste%20Sub%20Plan%20and%20Tribal%20Area%20Sub%20Plan%20schemes%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20proper%20inspection%20or%20verification%20of%20the%20requisite%20documents%2C%20which%20indicated%20serious%20systemic%20lapses%20and%20resulted%20in%20many%20ineligible%20payments%20of%20subsidies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20light%20of%20the%20above%2C%20it%20is%20recommended%20that%20Tea%20Board%20should%20earmark%20stipulated%20budgetary%20allocation%20for%20Scheduled%20Caste%20Sub%20Plan%20and%20Tribal%20Area%20Sub%20Plan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fa-tea-garden-run-by-its-workers-what-was-and-what-could-have-been%5C%22%3EA%20Tea%20Garden%20Run%20By%20Its%20Workers%3A%20What%20Was%20and%20What%20Could%20Have%20Been%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Board%20may%20also%20initiate%20steps%20to%20investigate%20the%20cases%20of%20ineligible%20subsidy%20payments%20as%20these%20indicate%20corruption%2F%20fraud%20and%20accordingly%2C%20responsibility%20may%20be%20fixed%2C%20and%20an%20appropriate%20action%20may%20be%20taken.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%20Rs%201.55%20crore%20lying%20in%20the%20bank%20account%20of%20one%20beneficiary%20who%20could%20not%20set%20up%20a%20new%20factory%20within%20the%20time%20frame%20stipulated%20in%20scheme%20guidelines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20no%20recovery%20was%20initiated%20by%20Tea%20Board.%20Further%2C%20Tea%20Board%20disbursed%20excess%20subsidy%20of%20Rs%202.05%20crore%20to%2023%20tea%20estates%20for%20creation%20of%20irrigation%20facilities%20for%20areas%20exceeding%20the%20approved%20limits%20as%20per%20scheme%20guidelines%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmid%20rising%20instances%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbengal-tea-gardens-workers-rights%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edistress%20to%20tea%20garden%20workers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20audit%20has%20also%20found%20that%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202021%2C%2015%20big%20gardens%20of%20north%20and%20south%20India%20remained%20closed%20affecting%20the%20livelihood%20of%2012%2C039%20permanent%20and%204%2C480%20temporary%20workers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20general%20reasons%20for%20sickness%20or%20closure%20were%20attributed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cpoor%20garden%20management%20practices%2C%20falling%20quality%20and%20price%20realisations%2C%20labour%20unrest%2C%20lack%20of%20development%20perspective%2C%20high%20debt-oriented%20funding%20strategy%2C%20ownership%20disputes%20etc%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20the%20Tea%20Board%20had%20not%20adequately%20inspected%20factories%20during%202016-17%20to%202020-21.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20shortfall%20of%20inspection%20ranged%20between%2078.62%25%20and%2091.95%25%20which%20showed%20poor%20monitoring%20on%20part%20of%20Tea%20Board%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20Tea%20Board%20is%20meant%20to%20direct%20its%20officials%20to%20collect%20tea%20samples%20from%20the%20manufacturing%20units%20and%20send%20them%20to%20authorised%20laboratories%20for%20testing%20for%20quality%20assurance%2C%20once%20in%20six%20months.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20found%20that%20there%20was%20a%20shortfall%20in%20sample%20collection%20ranging%20between%2084%25and%2097%25%20during%20the%20audit%20period%20indicating%20%E2%80%9Cpoor%20monitoring.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%20small%20tea%20growers%20contributed%20towards%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20total%20tea%20production%20in%202020-2021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20well-defined%20strategy%20for%20identification%20and%20registration%20of%20the%20small%20tea%20growers%2C%2038%25%20of%20small%20tea%20growers%20were%20not%20registered%20as%20of%20March%202021%20and%20were%20out%20of%20the%20ambit%20of%20Tea%20Board%E2%80%99s%20regulatory%20activities%20and%20developmental%20assistance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20hundred%20and%20nineteen%20out%20of%201%2C573%20big%20tea%20growers%20were%20not%20registered%20as%20of%20March%202021%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20the%20illegal%20practice%20of%20mixing%20Nepal%20tea%20with%20Darjeeling%20tea%20is%20still%20continuing%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20would%20ultimately%20dilute%20the%20quality%20of%20world-famous%20Darjeeling%20tea.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F07%2F4462362790_1db1b984ba_o.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221235%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F07%2F4462362790_1db1b984ba_o.jpg%201235w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F07%2F4462362790_1db1b984ba_o-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F07%2F4462362790_1db1b984ba_o-1024x679.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-7577%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22819%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20report%20also%20found%20that%20small%20tea%20growers%20contributed%20towards%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20total%20tea%20production%20in%202020-2021.%E2%80%99%20Photo%3A%20nallin%20a%2C%20CC%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENon%2Fshort%20payment%20of%20GST%20by%20Department%20of%20Post%20worth%20Rs%2042.48%20crores%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20CAG%20report%20on%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Faudit-report%2Fdetails%2F119132%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECompliance%20Audit%20on%20Finance%20and%20Communication%2C%20Union%20Government%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20contains%20significant%20findings%20from%20the%20compliance%20audit%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Communications%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%2C%20and%20Ministry%20of%20Finance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20the%20Department%20of%20Posts%20(DoP)%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Communication%20did%20not%20formulate%20a%20conservation%20policy%20of%20its%20own%20to%20meet%20the%20requirements%20of%20protection%20and%20conservation%20of%20Heritage%20Buildings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20funds%20allocated%20to%20the%20Department%20for%20its%20mandated%20activities%20were%20inadequate.%20Inadequate%20planning%20and%20poor%20management%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20absence%20of%20periodical%20physical%20verification%20further%20aggravated%20the%20dilapidated%20condition%20of%20the%20Heritage%20Buildings.%20Thus%2C%20the%20Department%20lacked%20the%20required%20sense%20of%20purpose%20and%20an%20appropriate%20strategy%20for%20the%20conservation%20and%20protection%20of%20its%20Heritage%20Buildings%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20DoP%20had%20incurred%20non-%20or%20short-payment%20of%20GST%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2042.48%20crores%20during%20the%20period%20from%202018-19%20to%202021-22.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%20this%20was%20because%20DoP%20%E2%80%9Cfailed%20to%20issue%20instructions%20to%20its%20subordinate%20offices%20to%20pay%20the%20GST%20on%20reverse%20charge%20basis%20on%20the%20commission%20paid%20to%20its%20sales%20force%20for%20procurement%20of%20Postal%20Life%20Insurance%2FRural%20Postal%20Life%20Insurance%20policies%20which%20resulted%20in%20non%20%2F%20short-payment%20of%20GST%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2042.48%20crore%20during%20the%20period%20from%202018-19%20to%202021-22.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%20DoP%20also%20failed%20to%20segregate%20the%20financial%20assistance%20received%20from%20UIDAI%20on%20Aadhaar%20related%20services%20between%20its%20own%20revenue%20and%20Goods%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%20component%20which%20%E2%80%9Cresulted%20in%20non%2Fshort-payment%20of%20GST%20amounting%20to%20Rs%209.00%20crore%20for%20the%20period%20from%20May%202018%20to%20July%202022.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpoor%2Finefficient%20planning%20coupled%20with%20ineffective%20monitoring%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20(MeitY)%20led%20to%20wasteful%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%2021.83%20crore%20on%20establishment%20of%20the%20Electronics%20Test%20and%20Development%20Centre%20(ETDC)%20Ajmer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20centre%20is%20meant%20for%20test%20and%20calibration%20of%20large%20area%20solar%20photo%20voltaic%20panel%20and%20telecom%20equipment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20audit%20also%20found%20that%20the%20Bharat%20Sanchar%20Nigam%20Limited%20or%20BSNL%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Communications%20which%20is%20in%20possession%20of%20substantial%20land%20and%20real%20estate%20holdings%2C%20has%20not%20instituted%20a%20comprehensive%20Estate%20Management%20Policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20assurances%20to%20the%20Public%20Accounts%20Committee%20(PAC)%2C%20%E2%80%9CBSNL%20has%20incomplete%20records%20of%20ownership%20of%20its%20real%20estate%2C%20hindering%20utilisation%20of%20its%20assets%20through%20sale%20or%20rental.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20said%20that%20BSNL%20procured%206%2C000%20Aadhaar%20Enrolment%20Kits%20during%202018-19%20worth%20Rs%2077.88%20crore.%20%E2%80%9COut%20of%20them%2C%203%2C941%20kits%20remained%20non-operational%20till%20December%202022.%20This%20resulted%20in%20blockade%20of%20Government%20funds%20of%20Rs%2051.15%20crore%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20part%20one%20of%20the%20series%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-nhai-toll-collection-railway-bharatmala-udan%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692350104000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18114050%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-reports-government-corruption-tea-board-khadi-bsnl-swadesh-darshan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20part%20two%20of%20this%20series%2C%20'The%20Wire'%20looks%20at%20what%20four%20of%2012%20reports%20filed%20by%20the%20CAG%20say%20on%20corruption%20in%20key%20departments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-reports-government-corruption-tea-board-khadi-bsnl-swadesh-darshan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Provide%20borrowers%20option%20to%20switch%20to%20fixed%20interest%20rates%3A%20RBI%20to%20banks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692349446000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Fmisc%2F2022-06%2F08%2Ffull%2Freserve-bank-of-india-rbi-1654678790-46973100.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fprovide-borrowers-option-to-switch-to-fixed-interest-rates-rbi-to-banks-123081800351_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20order%20to%20address%20these%20concerns%2C%20RBI%20asked%20entities%20regulated%20by%20it%20to%20put%20in%20place%20an%20appropriate%20policy%20framework%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagem