0publications%20to%20remove%20the%20defamatory%20article%20from%20their%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20years%20to%20build%20a%20reputation%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20right%20to%20reputation%20has%20been%20recognised%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%2C%20per%20the%20news%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20doubt%2C%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20provides%20the%20right%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20to%20all%20persons%2C%20however%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20overlooked%20that%20the%20same%20is%20subject%20to%20restrictions%20under%20Article%2019(2)%20which%20includes%20defamation.%20The%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20cannot%20be%20taken%20as%20an%20unfettered%20right%20so%20as%20to%20defame%20and%20tarnish%20the%20reputation%20of%20another%20person.%20It%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20held%20by%20Courts%20that%20fundamental%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20has%20to%20be%20counterbalanced%20with%20the%20right%20of%20reputation%20of%20an%20individual.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20said%20that%20prima%20facie%2C%3Cem%3E%20Organiser%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Commune%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20the%20articles%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20reckless%20manner%20without%20any%20factual%20verification%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20the%20news%20coverage%20was%20harming%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20school%20principal.%20The%20principal%20is%20a%20well-regarded%20individual%20within%20the%20country%20and%20has%20affiliations%20with%20multiple%20educational%20establishments%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20the%20school%20principal%20has%20presented%20a%20strong%20case%20in%20his%20favour.%20The%20principal%20said%20that%20as%20long%20as%20these%20articles%20remain%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20there%20is%